name: js-wildcard-destructure
backends: [int, js]
---

# `_` wildcard in tuple destructuring, used twice (js-wildcard-destructure-dup)

A `_` wildcard in a `val (x, _) = …` binding was emitted as the literal JS identifier
`_`, so two such bindings in one scope collided with "Identifier '_' has already been
declared". Each wildcard now gets a fresh unique throwaway name.

```scalascript
val (a, _) = (1, 2)
val (b, _) = (3, 4)
val (_, c) = (5, 6)
println(a + b + c)
```
